At level 62, trees, spiders, ravens etc, all mobs around GY yield roughly 2.2% AA exp.  I was averaging roughly 22% aa exp each hour.  I'm sure others could get much more, but my gear sucks and I need to med a lot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway I usually set up camp north of GY on the wall near where a static blood raven spawns.  My method is simple aggro kiting, load up 61 air pet, equip it with muzzle, belt, fists, and give it burnout (no need for DS).  I get at max range for FBOT, fire off 2 FBOT run back to pet, sick pet, and just kite it around.  I've found I like air pet better than water pet just because I can kill al ot faster because 1 the stuns are huge aggro on mob, and 2 the stuns stop the mob from chasing me giving me time to stop and nuke again.  Usually pet ends up like 75% hp (which he regens in like 30 seconds), and I end up spending 40mana on the mob..  Pretty much completely safe with run3 or jboots, if you get an add just zone out...<br>
<br>
For fun the other day I was in a group around Lower zone out (the zone out next to hedge) killing banshees and wraiths.  Anyway group broke up, I thought hell, there is a nice long open wall here with no wanderers, I'll try soloin !! Well banshees there summon, so they definately a no go for me, didn't even want to try them since my method is aggro kiting and I only have 52 pet heal..  Anyway I just stuck with wraiths..<br>
<br>
I was getting 4% aa a kill solo with wraiths and 2%aa duoing with a druid using same methods.  Same methods as above, 2 FBOT, sick pet, aggro kite and finish with more FBOT.  Wraiths drop parchments, and there is a zone out right there.. The walls have no mobs so very nice place to kite.  ONly problem is its usually camped <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway , PON is a great zone, glad I read this thread and gave it a shot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
